üé® Inpainting is your "undo" button when AI decides to bless you with three-armed nightmares.

Step 1: Load an image.

Step 2: Right-click on the load image node. ‚Üí Spend 5 minutes looking for "Open in Mask Editor." üïµÔ∏è

 Step 3: Realize how **annoying** that is.

Inpainting isn‚Äôt just for cursed limbs. You can use it to swap outfits, recolor hair, or rewrite reality one brushstroke at a time. üòé

nodes.title: ‚ö° Flux Advanced ‚Äì RunPod Edition

Welcome, **Noodler** üçú. Yes, I'm still calling you that. üôÇ

Max has us **wiggling** into the deep end with Adetailer, Inpainting, and Outpainting, aka the holy trinity of AI touch-ups with a side of Upscaling. üçú

Level 1 was your cozy island üèùÔ∏è Level 2 drops you into the jungle üå¥. Don‚Äôt worry, I‚Äôm still here, still noodling, still slightly unhinged. üòú

nodes.title: The Real Deal
widgets_values:
This is where the **real** upscaling magic lives.

Pick your upscale model. Don‚Äôt stress about being picky, Flux is gonna clean up the mess anyway.

Set your "Upscale By" amount in the upscale node based on the model you use (x2 or x4), and as always‚Ä¶ keep an eye on denoise strength.
Higher = wild changes. Lower = keepin‚Äô it close. üéØ

Ignore the other settings. Let 'em do their thing.
They‚Äôre background actors. You‚Äôre the director now. üé¨

Pro tip: The steps here are 10. Raise and compare if you like.

nodes.title: üòî The Last Noodle?
widgets_values:
You're either dedicated or you've gotten lost clicking noodles and somehow ended up here. Either way, **respect**. ü´°

So, what's next? üéØ

Go forth and experiment wildly or brace yourself, because Level 3 is packing a lot. 

- Pulid, generate new images that keep a consistent face. 

- Redux, use the style of an image as a prompt. 

- Depth, strip the soul out of an image and prompt for what Flux should fill it with. 

- Canny, Depth's weird cousin that likes edge maps instead of depth maps. 

- And more üôÇ

All you have to do is go back to RunPod and click "‚ö° Unlock Mega Workflow".

nodes.title: A Word From Max
widgets_values:
Building this RunPod template took a huge amount of time. Figuring out Patreon authentication, RunPod quirks, adapting the workflow, and tons and tons of testing was no weekend project. ü•≤

If you're subscribed to Power Users, you‚Äôre not just unlocking the Mega Flux Workflow. You‚Äôre literally making it possible for me to keep supporting RunPod users such as yourself. Like adding SDXL, Flux Kontext, and every future workflow I make. 

So I have to be real. If there's no support, I can't justify the time it takes to make these templates and port over future workflows. So if you sub just know: 

**You're the reason any of this is exists.**
